EMSHEIMER v. CITY OF NEW ORLEANS. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. February 10, 1903.) No. 971. Appeal from the Circuit Court of the United States for the Eastern District of Louisiana. J. D. Rouse and William Grant, for appellant. Samuel L. Gilmore, City Atty., Frank B. Thomas, Asst. City Atty., and Branch K. Miller, for appellee.

Before PARDEE, McCORMICK, and SHELBY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The decree of the circuit court is affirmed. Emsheimer v. City of New Orleans (C. C.) 116 Fed. 893; Id., 186 U. S. 33, 22 Sup. Ct. 770, 46 L. Ed. 1042.

PARDEE, Circuit Judge, dissents.
